cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.SI 

This paper discusses a game-theoretic model for security and proposes a reactive defense algorithm inspired by online learning theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The game-theoretic aspect of the paper could also place it under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and the robustness analysis could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
